-- Greece's NBG hires Goldman, Morgan Stanley to manage share offering-source
-- By George Georgiopoulos
-- Mon Apr 14, 2014 05:21AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, April 14 (Reuters) - Greece's largest lender National Bank <NBGr.AT> has picked Goldman Sachs <GS.N> and Morgan Stanley <MS.N> as global coordinators for a planned equity offering to plug its 2.18 billion euro capital shortfall, a senior banker familiar with the issue told Reuters on Monday on condition of anonymity.

